    "summary": "Upstash exposes HTTP APIs for its Developer API, Redis REST, QStash, Vector, and Search, plus a CLI; recorded auth is Basic auth with account email + Developer API key for the Developer API/CLI, Bearer or query-token auth for Redis and QStash, Bearer auth for Vector, and Search uses a per-database REST URL/token but its exact wire auth was not confirmed.",
    "credentials": {
      "upstash_dev_api_key": {
        "type": "basic",
        "label": "Upstash Developer API credentials (account email + API key)",
        "generateUrl": "https://console.upstash.com/account/api",
        "setup": "In the [Upstash Console API Keys page](https://console.upstash.com/account/api), create an API key under `Account` → `Management API` / `API Keys`, then use your Upstash account email together with that API key. The docs state the Developer API uses HTTP Basic auth with `EMAIL` as the username and `API_KEY` as the password.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "upstash_redis_rest_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Upstash Redis REST token",
        "setup": "Create or open a Redis database in the [Upstash Console Redis section](https://console.upstash.com/redis). On the database page, copy the `HTTPS` endpoint and the `Token` (or `Readonly Token`) from the connection details. The docs say to use that token for Redis REST API authorization.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "upstash_qstash_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Upstash QStash token",
        "generateUrl": "https://console.upstash.com/qstash",
        "setup": "Open the [Upstash Console QStash page](https://console.upstash.com/qstash) and copy your `QSTASH_TOKEN`. The docs say this token is used to authenticate requests to the QStash API.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "upstash_vector_rest_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Upstash Vector REST token",
        "setup": "Create or open a vector index in the Upstash console, then in the index details `Connect` section select the `cURL` tab and copy `UPSTASH_VECTOR_REST_URL` and `UPSTASH_VECTOR_REST_TOKEN`. The docs show this token in the `Authorization: Bearer` header for the Vector REST API.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "upstash_search_rest_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Upstash Search REST token",
        "setup": "Create or open a Search database in Upstash, then copy the search REST credentials shown for SDK/REST access: `UPSTASH_SEARCH_REST_URL` and `UPSTASH_SEARCH_REST_TOKEN`. The Search docs show these values being supplied to the client for API access.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
    },
